      <bioghist id="aspace_736f27d596ca25b8df91a28644574f91">
         <head>Historical Note</head>
         <p>The U.S. Census Bureau conducts a nationwide census every 10 years. Census 2000 sought
            to count and classify a record number of the American population, emphasizing the
            changing demographics of the country. This collection was donated to the John W. Hartman
            Center for Sales, Advertising, &amp; Marketing History by Sybil F. Stershic, a member of
            the Census Advisory Committee of Professional Associations for Census 2000.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3318010c9eb0e23c916636a161fe7a22">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>The collection includes a Census 2000 advertising binder, several informational and
            promotional posters, a partnership informational kit, and two special reports. There are
            also two VHS tapes with advertisements from the Census 2000 campaign. Acquired as part
            of the John W. Hartman Center for Sales, Advertising, &amp; Marketing History.</p>
      </scopecontent>
